{
  "texts": [
    "It should be noted that only 17 respondents were foundation level students and the relationship was significant but moderate.",
    "The second part of the survey began to focus on the student's knowledge, use and opinions of GAI technologies.",
    "They were asked if prior to completing the survey, if they had heard of any of the listed technologies.",
    "Grammarly (known by 88.5% of participants) and ChatGPT (known by 68.9%) were most widely heard of (Fig. 2).",
    "The following question asked if the students had used or considered using these technologies, what their purpose was for using them."
  ]
}